NOTE ON LICENSE SCOPE

Only the `iv-thumb` binary (this crate) is distributed under GPL-2.0-or-later.
The main `iv` image viewer (the parent crate) remains MIT-licensed and is
distributed independently. See ../LICENSE for the MIT terms covering `iv`.

The GPL obligation applies to `iv-thumb` because it statically links x265
(GPL-2.0-or-later) via libheif in order to encode HEVC thumbnails natively
(matching iPhone/camera-produced HEIC files). Building `iv-thumb` therefore
requires `libheif[core,aom,x265]` in vcpkg; see Cargo.toml.
